        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 11 at 6:40PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 640 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Toston, or 8 miles south of Townsend, moving north at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Townsend, Silos, and Radersburg.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
